{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-19T22:51:33.069Z","tool_name":"run_shell_command","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1776639093069_0","parameters":{"description":"Create a README.md file in the papers directory with a summary of the downloaded papers and their relevance to the research.","command":"cat > papers/README.md << 'EOF'\n# Downloaded Papers\n\nThis directory contains research papers relevant to the investigation of induction heads and their role in leakage/repetition.\n\n1.  **In-context Learning and Induction Heads** (Olsson et al., 2022)\n    -   `2209.11895v1_In-context_Learning_and_Induction_Heads.pdf`\n    -   *Why relevant*: Seminal paper defining induction heads and their link to ICL.\n\n2.  **Induction Head Toxicity Mechanistically Explains Repetition Curse in Large Language Models** (Shuxun Wang et al., 2025)\n    -   `Induction_Head_Toxicity_v1.pdf`\n    -   *Why relevant*: Directly addresses how induction head \"toxicity\" causes repetitive generation (leakage).\n\n3.  **The Evolution of Statistical Induction Heads: In-Context Learning Markov Chains** (Edelman et al., 2024)\n    -   `2402.11004v1_The_Evolution_of_Statistical_Induction_Heads_In-Co.pdf`\n    -   *Why relevant*: Studies how transformers learn in-context statistics, which might be a source of leakage.\n\n4.  **Next-token pretraining implies in-context learning** (Riechers et al., 2025)\n    -   `2505.18373v2_Next-token_pretraining_implies_in-context_learning.pdf`\n    -   *Why relevant*: Links pretraining data properties to the emergence of induction heads and ICL.\n\n5.  **Language Models \"Grok\" to Copy** (Lv et al., 2024)\n    -   `2409.09281v2_Language_Models_\"Grok\"_to_Copy.pdf`\n    -   *Why relevant*: Connects the copying mechanism (induction heads) to training dynamics.\n\n6.  **Mechanistic Data Attribution: Tracing the Training Origins of Interpretable LLM Units** (Chen et al., 2026)\n    -   `2601.21996v1_Mechanistic_Data_Attribution_Tracing_the_Training_.pdf`\n    -   *Why relevant*: Shows how repetitive structural data in training catalyzes induction heads.\n\n7.  **Overthinking the Truth: Understanding how Language Models Process False Demonstrations** (Halawi et al., 2023)\n    -   `2307.09476_Overthinking_the_Truth.pdf`\n    -   *Why relevant*: Identifies \"false induction heads\" that attend to and copy false information from previous demonstrations.\n\n8.  **Understanding and Controlling Repetition Neurons and Induction Heads in In-Context Learning** (2025)\n    -   `2507.07810_Repetition_Neurons_Induction_Heads.pdf`\n    -   *Why relevant*: Directly addresses controlling repetition driven by induction heads.\nEOF\n"}}
