e investigation of induction heads and their role in leakage/repetition.\n\n1.  **TransformerLens** (github.com/neelnanda-io/TransformerLens)\n    -   *Purpose*: Essential library for mechanistic interpretability of transformers.\n    -   *Location*: `code/TransformerLens/`\n    -   *Key functionality*: Causal interventions, activation patching, attention visualization.\n\n2.  **Generalized Induction-Head (GIM)** (github.com/ejkim47/generalized-induction-head)\n    -   *Purpose*: Implementation of the GIM paper's retrieval-based next-token prediction.\n    -   *Location*: `code/GIM/`\n    -   *Key functionality*: Retrieval-based module for in-context information.\n\n3.  **Evolution of Statistical Induction Heads** (github.com/EzraEdelman/Evolution-of-Statistical-Induction-Heads)\n    -   *Purpose*: Code for the paper \"The Evolution of Statistical Induction Heads\".\n    -   *Location*: `code/Evolution-of-Statistical-Induction-Heads/`\n    -   *Key functionality*: Data generation for Markov Chain ICL tasks.\n\n4.  **MarkovICL** (github.com/Simon-Lepage/MarkovICL)\n    -   *Purpose*: Alternative implementation for Markov Chain ICL.\n    -   *Location*: `code/MarkovICL/`\n    -   *Key functionality*: Markov Chain simulation and ICL evaluation.\n\n5.  **Surgeon** (github.com/gussand/surgeon)\n    -   *Purpose*: Code for \"Even Heads Fix Odd Errors\" paper.\n    -   *Location*: `code/surgeon/`\n    -   *Key functionality*: Head-level intervention and \"repair\" techniques.\nEOF\n"}}
